The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Tuesday, July 06, 2004 				 Gratuity freeze off
																								Calcutta, July 5: Finance minister Asim Dasgupta today lifted the freeze on gratuity for retired schoolteachers and recruitment of non-teaching staff in government-sponsored institutions.																								The freeze moves were a fallout of the governments financial crunch and in place for the past three years.																								Announcing the end of the recruitment bar in the Assembly, Dasgupta said the decision would help solve problems affecting the day-to-day activities of sponsored schools.																								Teachers who have retired in the mean time will also get their dues now.
